  <title>Symmetry and Group Theory</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      This resource is designed for chemistry graduate students who are seeking a more mathematical approach to learning about point groups and group theory. 
      We assume the reader has taken inorganic chemistry and the quantum portion of physical chemistry, both at an undergraduate level. 
      We also assume familiarity with basic multivariate calculus, basic linear algebra, and with the main conclusions of chemistry group theoretic concepts. 
    </p>
    <p> 
      Because we are not aiming to be a student's first exposure to group theory and its applications in chemistry, it is prudent for us to outline a few particularly useful and/or popular resources. 
      Here are a few: 
    </p>
